This paper is primarily focused on the machine learning aspect of federated learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, it also deals with the wireless communication aspect of FL, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses scheduling policies, which can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to scheduling based on the significance of local model updates, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
